FT  08 OCT 94 / More gas jobs go
A further 325 British Gas jobs are to disappear from northern England as
part of the com-pany's reorganisation. A total of 225 administration workers
in British Gas's service group, based at Sunderland, Carlisle and Thornaby
in Cleveland are being offered the chance to transfer to offices at
Uddingston, near Glasgow, and 100 store workers at a British Gas centre in
Newcastle upon Tyne have been asked to consider moving to Leicestershire.
